Lado Kham was a Slovenian architect and engineer who graduated from the Technical University of Vienna. He worked on various construction projects in Austria and Slovenia, including apartment buildings in Vienna and Ljubljana, a Catholic church in Germany, and the renovation of a monastic church in Deutsch Schützen.
